						<summary>

						<p>It records a gift of 325 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land by Aṭṭamūrti, son of Pēraiyya Nalluḻāṉ Ūraḍi, a resident of Saṅkarappāḍi at Rajāmallach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, to the deity Dakshiṇāmūrtti for providing food offerings and worship. It is also stated that the said land was situated in south of Paramēsvara Vāykkāl, was purchased by his father from Naṟaiyūr Chaṇḍiśarmanār.</p>						

						</summary>
